HLS 26RS-5950 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 348
BY REPRESENTATIVE WALTERS
FUNERALS & FUNERAL HOMES: Creates a subcommittee of the House Committee on
Commerce to study funeral planning regulation or oversight
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create a subcommittee to be comprised of members of the House Committee on
3 Commerce to study whether persons working as funeral planners, funeral arrangers,
4 end-of-life doulas, death doulas, or under any similar designation should be subject
5 to state regulation, credentialing, and oversight, and to make recommendations for
6 policy and legislative changes on or before November 1, 2026.
7 WHEREAS, demand for paid funeral planning and end-of-life doula services has
8 expanded rapidly in recent years, while no state in the United States currently requires
9 government licensure or certification to practice as a funeral planner or an end-of-life doula,
10 and the most prominent national organization in the field, the National End-of-Life Doula
11 Alliance, offers only a voluntary proficiency credential and does not accredit or evaluate any
12 training program; and
13 WHEREAS, the absence of any state credentialing, bonding, or licensure requirement
14 for persons offering paid funeral planning or end-of-life doula services in this state creates
15 risks for licensed funeral directors and funeral homes, including the receipt of undisclosed
16 referral fees or insurance commissions, the unauthorized acceptance of consumer payments
17 for goods or services to be delivered upon death, exposure of licensed funeral establishments
18 to civil liability arising from the acts of unlicensed third parties, and consumer confusion
19 regarding qualifications and accountability, all of which warrant further study.
20 WHEREAS, this state licenses funeral directors, embalmers, funeral establishments,
21 and crematory authorities through the Louisiana State Board of Embalmers and Funeral
