1 through R.S. 37:866, and any other applicable provisions of the law and administrative codes
2 of this state; ought to be enacted.
3 (4) Contractual disclosure, transparency, and right-of-cancellation requirements, and
4 whether a consumer complaint, investigation, and disciplinary process is warranted,
5 including civil penalties and grounds for denial, suspension, or revocation of any license.
6 (5) The allocation of civil and criminal liability between licensed funeral
7 establishments and unlicensed funeral planners or end-of-life doulas, and any necessary safe
8 harbor or due diligence framework for licensed establishments interacting with such persons.
9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the subcommittee shall hold public hearings to
10 receive testimony from any interested party and shall specifically solicit advice and guidance
11 from the Louisiana Funeral Directors Association, the Louisiana Funeral Directors and
12 Morticians Association, the Louisiana Cemetery Association, and other funeral industry
13 professionals.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the chair of the House Committee on Commerce
15 or his designee shall serve as chair of the subcommittee at its initial meeting, to be held on
16 or before August 1, 2026.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
18 president of the Louisiana Funeral Directors Association, the president of the Louisiana
19 Funeral Directors and Morticians Association, and the president of the Louisiana Cemetery
20 Association.
